1
00:00:06,233 --> 00:00:07,967
Good job today.

2
00:00:07,967 --> 00:00:09,500
Kentaro.

3
00:00:09,500 --> 00:00:11,767
I have to go to Korea.

4
00:00:11,767 --> 00:00:14,333
What? What do you mean?

5
00:00:14,333 --> 00:00:18,100
It's political sponsorship night tomorrow.

6
00:00:18,100 --> 00:00:21,000
Something more important came up.

7
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:23,433
The mayor said it's a dinner you must attend.

8
00:00:23,433 --> 00:00:27,033
To attract investment
for a Japanese theme park in Dongcheon City,

9
00:00:27,033 --> 00:00:28,700
he said you must meet him.

10
00:00:28,700 --> 00:00:31,867
I can make it back on time.

11
00:00:31,867 --> 00:00:34,100
Is it because of Seo Yi Do?

12
00:00:35,100 --> 00:00:38,533
Didn't Hyeon go to handle it?

13
00:00:38,533 --> 00:00:40,133
Don't you trust Hyeon?

14
00:00:40,133 --> 00:00:42,667
Hyeon hasn't contacted me.

15
00:00:42,667 --> 00:00:46,533
I think I need to go check
what's going on myself.

16
00:00:46,533 --> 00:00:49,433
- Still...
- I have to meet Yi Do myself.

17
00:00:49,433 --> 00:00:53,533
I know him best.

18
00:00:53,533 --> 00:00:56,867
He would never disobey me.

19
00:00:58,233 --> 00:01:01,233
I've been wondering for a while,

20
00:01:01,967 --> 00:01:05,567
why are you so obsessed with Seo Yi Do?

21
00:01:05,567 --> 00:01:09,933
Why do you always treat
that idiot differently?

22
00:01:09,933 --> 00:01:12,133
Don't talk nonsense.

23
00:01:12,133 --> 00:01:16,467
Honestly, that punk is getting out of line.

24
00:01:17,667 --> 00:01:20,367
Shall I take care of him?

25
00:01:22,533 --> 00:01:25,967
If you say that one more time,

26
00:01:26,667 --> 00:01:29,033
I won't let this slide.

27
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:32,967
I'll talk to the mayor myself,

28
00:01:32,967 --> 00:01:37,200
so you, stay out of this.

29
00:02:18,733 --> 00:02:20,433
It suits you well.

30
00:02:22,800 --> 00:02:25,067
What happened?

31
00:02:26,067 --> 00:02:28,067
Heo Dong Hwa shot a gun.

32
00:02:28,067 --> 00:02:31,167
So you killed Heo Dong Hwa?

33
00:02:35,533 --> 00:02:37,767
Why did you let Heo Dong Hwa go?

34
00:02:43,400 --> 00:02:47,767
You're not telling me on purpose, aren't you?
About Chu Tae Jeong.

35
00:02:49,433 --> 00:02:53,067
- You didn't obey my order to kill him.
- He ran away.

36
00:02:53,067 --> 00:02:54,767
Ran away?

37
00:02:56,633 --> 00:02:58,467
I have no excuses.

38
00:03:10,967 --> 00:03:12,700
Liar.

39
00:03:14,633 --> 00:03:17,000
You had no intention of killing him.

40
00:03:24,133 --> 00:03:28,167
Why don't you listen to me
even though you know I care about you?

41
00:03:28,167 --> 00:03:31,533
I trusted and raised you for 15 years,

42
00:03:33,333 --> 00:03:35,800
and you make me look like a fool like this?

43
00:03:38,067 --> 00:03:41,000
- I wasn't trying to.
- Seo Yi Do!

44
00:03:45,933 --> 00:03:47,633
On your 17th birthday,

45
00:03:47,633 --> 00:03:50,433
do you remember the stowaway
from Gunsan to Japan?

46
00:03:50,433 --> 00:03:53,967
Everyone said it would be impossible,
but you caught him in a day.

47
00:03:55,200 --> 00:03:57,567
- That...
- Take care of it this time too.

48
00:03:58,467 --> 00:04:01,700
Catching those who run away
is what you do best.

49
00:04:05,867 --> 00:04:08,833
That punk was here last night too, right?

50
00:04:08,833 --> 00:04:10,933
He can't have gone far yet.

51
00:04:10,933 --> 00:04:13,400
Then he might still be in Dongcheon.

52
00:04:16,567 --> 00:04:21,400
I'll help you. Just like old times.

53
00:04:26,500 --> 00:04:28,233
I...

54
00:04:29,767 --> 00:04:31,600
I'll do it alone.

55
00:04:31,600 --> 00:04:33,300
No.

56
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:37,033
And after this job,

57
00:04:38,467 --> 00:04:40,033
I'll quit.

58
00:04:40,033 --> 00:04:43,567
So this is what you wanted to say all along.

59
00:04:43,567 --> 00:04:48,267
Don't you know what it means
for people like us to quit?

60
00:04:48,267 --> 00:04:51,100
I want to live an ordinary life.

61
00:04:51,100 --> 00:04:53,767
What are you talking about?

62
00:04:53,767 --> 00:04:57,100
There's no such thing
as an ordinary life, Seo Yi Do.

63
00:04:57,100 --> 00:04:58,833
Yes, there is.

64
00:04:58,833 --> 00:05:00,833
I just didn't know it until now.

65
00:05:00,833 --> 00:05:03,200
The moment you quit,

66
00:05:03,200 --> 00:05:06,567
you'll be a killer living in fear,
not knowing when you'll die.

67
00:05:06,567 --> 00:05:11,133
Don't choose a life of despair.
I won't allow it.

68
00:05:11,133 --> 00:05:13,267
I don't care.

69
00:05:14,833 --> 00:05:21,067
The world doesn't welcome people like us.
Even if we disappear, no one cares.

70
00:05:21,067 --> 00:05:23,200
That's not true.

71
00:05:23,200 --> 00:05:27,467
The mayor of Dongcheon
will soon run for President.

72
00:05:27,467 --> 00:05:31,000
- We'll be well off by his side.
- I don't want that anymore.

73
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:34,500
That's just greed.
You want happiness after killing so many?

74
00:05:34,500 --> 00:05:36,700
You made me this way.

75
00:05:38,767 --> 00:05:40,900
Since I was young.

76
00:05:42,600 --> 00:05:44,333
Isn't that right?

77
00:05:46,233 --> 00:05:48,900
I'm the one who saved you.

78
00:05:48,900 --> 00:05:51,100
If you were going to raise me like this,

79
00:05:52,767 --> 00:05:55,133
you should have just killed me back then.

80
00:05:59,633 --> 00:06:01,367
Yi Do.

81
00:06:02,367 --> 00:06:05,933
I'm the one who knows you best.

82
00:06:05,933 --> 00:06:08,467
You're happiest by my side.

83
00:06:09,833 --> 00:06:11,567
Moo Gun.

84
00:06:12,433 --> 00:06:16,133
I wouldn't know that
unless I've experienced it myself.

85
00:06:16,133 --> 00:06:18,367
So please, stop.

86
00:06:21,267 --> 00:06:24,033
Chu Tae Jeong is going to die
by my hand anyway.

87
00:06:25,267 --> 00:06:28,600
Once he's gone,
you'll come to your senses again.

88
00:06:57,333 --> 00:06:59,067
Let us go.

89
00:07:00,533 --> 00:07:02,267
"Us"?

90
00:07:04,300 --> 00:07:07,800
What if you lose the other eye too?

91
00:07:07,800 --> 00:07:10,867
No one will look for a blind man.

92
00:07:11,700 --> 00:07:17,000
No one will try to help you except for me.

93
00:07:24,400 --> 00:07:26,133
Put the knife down.

94
00:07:28,633 --> 00:07:31,267
Why did you come here?

95
00:07:31,267 --> 00:07:33,300
I told you to leave!

96
00:07:36,433 --> 00:07:41,233
You knew it would come to this,
so you told me to leave, right?

97
00:07:45,500 --> 00:07:50,600
How nice. The prey
crawled right in on its own.

98
00:07:50,600 --> 00:07:55,333
Go ahead and shoot. I said shoot.

99
00:07:57,533 --> 00:08:02,533
So, am I going to die
by the son of the man I killed?

100
00:08:02,533 --> 00:08:03,633
Shut up.

101
00:08:03,633 --> 00:08:06,333
If you pull that trigger,
you'll just be a murderer.

102
00:08:06,333 --> 00:08:08,767
You can never go back to how things were,

103
00:08:08,767 --> 00:08:14,533
and that righteous cop act
will be impossible.

104
00:08:16,600 --> 00:08:20,600
Tae Jeong, stop.
You don't need to become a bad person too.

105
00:08:27,600 --> 00:08:31,200
Spare Tae Jeong. I'll go with you.

106
00:08:31,200 --> 00:08:34,800
You can only choose when I say so.

107
00:08:34,800 --> 00:08:36,400
Move.

108
00:08:36,400 --> 00:08:38,133
No.

109
00:09:00,533 --> 00:09:03,700
If you're going to leave me,
you might as well die.

110
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:26,733
I'm glad.

111
00:09:28,800 --> 00:09:31,367
That it wasn't you who killed me.

112
00:09:35,433 --> 00:09:37,167
Moo Gun.

113
00:10:00,400 --> 00:10:02,133
Are you okay?

114
00:10:08,933 --> 00:10:11,067
There's blood on your face.

115
00:10:11,700 --> 00:10:16,500
Don't worry. I'm fine.

116
00:10:16,500 --> 00:10:18,200
Yi Do.

117
00:10:18,833 --> 00:10:21,267
All that training was worth it.

118
00:10:24,533 --> 00:10:29,233
Let's go to a deserted beach
and live together.

119
00:10:31,767 --> 00:10:33,700
The place you used to like.

120
00:10:36,600 --> 00:10:41,100
Why aren't you answering? Don't you want to?

121
00:10:42,900 --> 00:10:46,733
I do. I'd like that.

122
00:10:50,700 --> 00:10:54,900
Make sure you uncover the truth
about your father's death.

123
00:10:54,900 --> 00:10:56,933
What are you talking about?

124
00:10:58,000 --> 00:11:00,633
We should handle it together.

125
00:11:00,633 --> 00:11:03,033
You were caught by me,

126
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:07,133
and I did everything.

127
00:11:07,133 --> 00:11:10,133
- Yi Do.
- If you care about me, do this for me.

128
00:11:22,600 --> 00:11:24,300
I love you.

129
00:11:25,333 --> 00:11:27,033
No.

130
00:12:00,267 --> 00:12:02,000
Tae Jeong.

131
00:12:02,700 --> 00:12:04,400
Forget me,

132
00:12:05,267 --> 00:12:07,267
and be happy.

133
00:12:08,967 --> 00:12:12,133
I'll remember the time with you until I die.

134
00:12:43,433 --> 00:12:45,267
Are you okay?

135
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:47,667
Yes.

136
00:12:47,667 --> 00:12:49,700
What's your name?

137
00:12:50,467 --> 00:12:53,633
I'm Chu Tae Jeong.

138
00:12:54,400 --> 00:12:56,600
You're a police officer.

139
00:12:58,133 --> 00:13:00,767
We've called an ambulance.
It'll be here soon.

140
00:13:01,433 --> 00:13:03,300
Thank you.

141
00:13:04,733 --> 00:13:06,433
Well...

142
00:13:07,533 --> 00:13:11,167
You're investigating criminal charges
related to the mayor, right?

143
00:13:11,167 --> 00:13:14,233
Do you know anything
about the criminal who attacked you?

144
00:13:14,233 --> 00:13:16,233
What?

145
00:13:16,233 --> 00:13:20,467
That person is the prime suspect
in the murder that occurred in the yard.

146
00:13:20,467 --> 00:13:22,000
We're currently searching.

147
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:25,500
Do you remember what he looks like
or any identifying details?

148
00:13:26,700 --> 00:13:29,933
You need to tell us everything you remember.

149
00:13:29,933 --> 00:13:33,933
The body in the yard is an employee
of the security company hired by the mayor,

150
00:13:33,933 --> 00:13:37,667
and there are indications
he's involved in violent crimes.

151
00:13:37,667 --> 00:13:40,300
We're also investigating right now...

152
00:13:57,600 --> 00:13:59,600
Oh, dear.

153
00:13:59,600 --> 00:14:01,833
- Don't you regret it?
- About what?

154
00:14:01,833 --> 00:14:03,867
You did so well lately.

155
00:14:03,867 --> 00:14:07,767
You solved the drug case
involving the mayor's son, right?

156
00:14:07,767 --> 00:14:10,400
I did it to clear my father's name.

157
00:14:10,400 --> 00:14:12,033
Since it was related.

158
00:14:12,033 --> 00:14:16,200
Still, HR said you're next in line
for promotion.

159
00:14:16,200 --> 00:14:19,000
Oh, it's such a waste.

160
00:14:20,533 --> 00:14:23,267
So what are your plans for the future?

161
00:14:23,267 --> 00:14:24,300
I don't know.

162
00:14:24,300 --> 00:14:26,867
They say if you quit
without a plan, you'll fail.

163
00:14:26,867 --> 00:14:29,167
Thanks for the kind words.

164
00:14:32,633 --> 00:14:35,567
Are you really not going to tell me
where you're going?

165
00:14:35,567 --> 00:14:37,100
We'll see.

166
00:14:37,100 --> 00:14:40,133
If you need anything, call me anytime.

167
00:14:40,967 --> 00:14:44,000
Okay, take care of yourself too.

168
00:14:44,000 --> 00:14:46,867
- I'll go now.
- Okay.

169
00:17:26,433 --> 00:17:29,567
How did you find me?

170
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:33,000
I came to buy a painting.

171
00:17:34,167 --> 00:17:36,533
You didn't sell it to someone else, did you?

172
00:17:39,467 --> 00:17:42,500
Painting suits you well.

173
00:17:45,733 --> 00:17:49,500
Why aren't you answering?
Are you mad that I came?

174
00:17:50,333 --> 00:17:52,067
No.

175
00:17:55,867 --> 00:17:57,833
What about work?

176
00:18:00,100 --> 00:18:01,900
I quit.

177
00:18:03,800 --> 00:18:06,533
I wanted to start fresh like you.

178
00:18:12,700 --> 00:18:14,500
I missed you.

179
00:18:15,400 --> 00:18:17,767
I missed you too.

180
00:18:17,767 --> 00:18:19,500
But...

181
00:18:23,367 --> 00:18:25,400
I have something to tell you.

182
00:18:27,067 --> 00:18:31,467
Actually, I'm a year younger than you.

183
00:18:32,367 --> 00:18:34,033
Huh?

184
00:18:34,033 --> 00:18:36,200
I missed you.
